Just started using fastlane for the first time, and ran into this issue, too. Took me a while to figure out that setting the code signing to manual in the Xcode project works.
definitely causing problems, either revert the PR or add a ENV var to bypass it ;)

I successfully change to manual signing during our build process - and use match and ENV var to pass to Gym to build. All works well...but auto never got working, as we create a number of apps (bundleIDs) from the same codebase.
Care to help out a noob and give an example how to use this ENV var to workaround this? Much appreciated!

Hope I can help. Coding is always about moving some data from A to B. In this case itâ€™s a provisioning profile reference, generated by sigh, for your build. I assume youâ€™re using manual code signing too. So, this is about passing the reference to gym which in turn passes this to an xcodebuild command.

The PROVISIONING_PROFILE_SPECIFIER is an ENV variable (environment that you're executing commands in such as terminal/bash) that is set with/as part of the xcodebuild command, just as you would set an ENV variable in a script, which Xcode uses to select the correct provision.

Sigh does in fact install the provision in a place where Xcode can reference it - once it has the uuid.

    udid = sigh(output_path: "./provisions")

    gym(scheme: â€œMasterProjectâ€,
	export_method: "app-store",
        clean: true,
	xcargs: "PROVISIONING_PROFILE_SPECIFIER='#{udid}'")

If you watch the output you will see sigh and gym execute, then issue an xcodebuild command with the xcargs passed.

Jules.
